result.execSummary:
The defendant Jacob A Baumbach was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

ADA Melissa Inlow appeared for the State.  Defendant appeared in person, in custody, with Attorney Osborne.  Defendant plead no contest to Count 1 as charged.  All other counts in 16CM74, plus 16CM165 all dismissed, but read in for sentencing purposes. Court recited the charge and possible penalties on the count he plead to.  Defendant understood.  Repeater allegation confirmed with the defendant.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  He understood.  Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of Misdemeanor Bail Jumping, contrary to 946.49(1)(a), as a repeater.  Joint recommendation for 5 months jail.  Concurrent to current prison sentence.  Court ordered:  5 months jail, concurrent to prison sentence now serving.  CC.  Pay by 10/1/17.  Find DNA sample has already been submitted.
